rComments: Would highly recommend taking this class with Professor Marques. He clearly cares about the success of his students and is very fair marker. Great lectures, which are asynch and you definitely need to listen to carefully for quizzes.  Really enjoyed attending the synch part of the class despite it being yet another online and evening course.

This was a great way to end my journey at Telfer. Prof and course were best part of degree for sure. Both the lectures and Intopia were awesome in different ways. Intopia was tough though and required A LOT of work upfront, and hard to get A. Rest of the course is easy to get an A as a long as you talk in class and study and listen to slides.

Every lecture was so interesting - so knowledgeable and genuinely interested in the content and making sure students do well. The case study format (where each lecture was applying last week's material to the case study of that week) was so interesting too. Intopia is tough but he helps where he can. One of my fave profs at telfer. Love him!

My favourite prof at Telfer - very knowledgeable and able to connect the dots. Would definitely recommend. Each lecture and case discussion was interesting and relevant. I hear his other course is pretty awesome too.

Fantastic prof. Quality of teaching including asynchronous content and cases given was very high. He's very responsive to emails and will take the time to meet with you and go over cases and intopia planing and issues. This was by far best course I took at Telfer because of him.

I honestly don't understand how this prof gets such a high rating. His synchronous classes feel more like a seminar than a lecture since all he does is talk about cases instead of how to help you complete Intopia. He said the case answers are open-ended but the feedback shows that they aren't. A piece of advice: find a super-smart team and u r fine

I would say he's an amazing prof and both his courses are great (I've taken both his 4311 and his 4319). He expects you to actively participate in class and speak up and there's quite a bit of material and preparation for intopia. But it's totally doable and i really enjoyed the lectures. Take him for sure.

Really enjoyed this course. Despite it being yet another online session, was completely different from the other courses. Professor Marquez was an excellent teacher and Intopia was a fantastic experience. He's very knowledgeable and conveys the material extremely well. Does a good job of relating what we cover in class to the simulation.

This is hands down one of the best courses that I have taken at Telfer. The professor's lectures were highly engaging and thought-provoking. Additionally, he was the only prof to truly recognize the impact of the pandemic on his students, and made a genuine effort to alleviate their stress by reducing some of the workload. I highly recommend!
Definitely take this prof. He's a absolute gem and his class was a real pleasure. Not an easy A but it was a great learning experience and I loved the material.

Really nice prof. The class initially seemed overwhelming and intimidating but he made several changes to the class to make it easier for students considering online classes (ex: final report went down from 50 --> 25 pages) which I really appreciated. Seemed pretty genuine and enthuastic about teaching this class too.

Prof Marquez is an amazing professor. He knows how to teach really well and has a great style. He put a lot of effort into the asyncronous part of the class and lectures were never dry or boring. He clearly wants you to learn about Emerging markets in a way that will make a difference to how you view the world. Watch out for hard quizzes though!
Totally agree with the previous comments. this course was my favorite from all the courses I did. It a bit more reading than other classes. The prof is excellent.

One of the best profs from the Telfer. I have taken both of his ADM4311 and ADM4319. He knows the content really well and able to help students after class. If your major is International Management, take his 4311 and 4319, you can learn a lot of useful international related content from his course.

He is an excellent prof. He knows the content well and able to help students after class. I have learned a lot from this course. This course does not have a textbook but has lots of online articles that need to be read. There are two synthesis reports; if you have read all the required articles carefully, you can easily get a good grade.

This professor is great. Lectures were entertaining and something to look forward to. He goes out of his way to make sure that students are engaged in the course, which happens to be one of the most interesting courses offered at Telfer. On the negative side, some of the group presentations were quite weak and bit of a time waster.

This prof was fantastic! I would definitely take one of his classes again. Very passionate about what he teaches which made going to class A LOT more interesting. A very approachable prof always available to help and cares about your success and progress. Assignments are doable but do require some good hard work.

Jose Carlos is one of the best and amazing professors at uOttawa and he is very nice and very approachable. I strongly recommend business students to take his class because you could learn a lot from him and enjoy excellent learning experience. In addition, Jose really cares about his students even if they have graduated from uOttawa. Best, best..

This class was great - opened my eyes to so much that I didn't know about business and developing countries. If you're doing international business I really recommend it strongly. Professor Marques was really impressive - very knowledgeable, super interesting and it shows that he really cares about his students.

Best, best, best professor at Telfer. Learned so much from his lectures. Was always interesting and so much I learned about poverty and the developing world. I only wish I had taken his strategy class too.

My best professor I've ever had. He made the class extremely enjoyable through his lecture style, slides and group activities. I agree with comments below that he's very passionate about development and international affairs and he's very engaging and thought-provoking. But you NEED to participate in class and read material to do well.
Hard quizzes worth 15% - not very fair
Really enjoyed his class and the intopia simulation. Best experience in my time at telfer.
il est excellent et sympa
dude is the LeBron James of Telfer

Passionate about teaching! The deliverables have unclear instructions - it is hard to distinguish what he is looking for in projects and assignments. Participation is graded harshly as well, I recommend taking this class if you are prepared to do weekly readings and are comfortable debating about them in class.

Really amazing Prof. He's very passionate and it shows he cares how much students learn. Really looked forward to classes - wish all my courses had been like this. He makes you work for it but I learned so much. Also, he's really nice to look at and listen to...

Overall good prof. Academic type prof; teaches the class like we are intelligent 4th year students unlike some other professors who still babysit. For strategic management, he gives two 7.5% quizzes which other professors do not. These quizzes are not an easy A (even though they are multiple choice) and add to an already heavy course with Intopia.
